<li>Wagner, Richard (ed. and tr. Stewart Spencer and Barry Millington) (1987), <i>Selected Letters of Richard Wagner</i>, London: Dent. <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt1126" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"}}'/><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/0-460-04643-8" title="Special:BookSources/0-460-04643-8">0-460-04643-8</a>; W. W. Norton and Company. <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt1128" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"}}'/><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-393-02500-2" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-393-02500-2">978-0-393-02500-2</a>.</li>
<li>Wagner, Richard (tr. Andrew Gray) (1992), <i><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Mein_Leben_(Wagner)" title="Mein Leben (Wagner)">My Life</a></i>, New York: Da Capo Press. <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt1130" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"}}'/><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-306-80481-6" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-306-80481-6">978-0-306-80481-6</a>. Wagner's partly unreliable autobiography, covering his life to 1864, written between 1865 and 1880 and first published privately in German in a small edition between 1870 and 1880. The first (edited) public edition appeared in 1911. Gray's translation is the most comprehensive available.</li>
